    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource block allocation in Service Request NAS message generation\n\n### Summary\nThe Service Request NAS message generation in the UE incorrectly allocated memory for the security protected message, leading to buffer overflows and corrupted MAC computation. This issue occurred when the UE had valid security contexts and attempted to send an integrity-protected Service Request.\n\nThe root cause was that the security header size was added to the total message size AFTER memory allocation, rather than before. This resulted in the allocated buffer being too small to accommodate the complete security protected message, causing memory corruption during encoding and integrity protection.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg.c`: Moved memory allocation to occur after security header size calculation in `generateServiceRequest()` function. Added proper memory allocation in both security protected and plain message branches.\n\n"
}